{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/auto-suggestions-and-syntax-highlighting/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Personal Blog","author":"Sonia Singla","lang":"en"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"55158487-662f-529b-ab86-4879a4dcb75a","excerpt":"As a developer, we spend a lot of time working on the terminal and having personalized shell makes the working environment perfect, decreases frustration andâ€¦","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4d418a1a3cd21c9e463202e015c97869/203d3/code.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 45.94594594594595%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"code\"\n        src=\"/static/4d418a1a3cd21c9e463202e015c97869/fcda8/code.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4d418a1a3cd21c9e463202e015c97869/12f09/code.png 148w,\n/static/4d418a1a3cd21c9e463202e015c97869/e4a3f/code.png 295w,\n/static/4d418a1a3cd21c9e463202e015c97869/fcda8/code.png 590w,\n/static/4d418a1a3cd21c9e463202e015c97869/efc66/code.png 885w,\n/static/4d418a1a3cd21c9e463202e015c97869/c83ae/code.png 1180w,\n/static/4d418a1a3cd21c9e463202e015c97869/203d3/code.png 1322w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<center><sub><sup>[Img src: https://undraw.co/illustrations]</sup></sub></center><br>\n<p>As a developer, we spend a lot of time working on the terminal and having personalized shell makes the working environment perfect, decreases frustration and also, increases productivity.</p>\n<p>In this blog, we will discuss how to quickly install plugins <code class=\"language-text\">Auto-Suggestions</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">Syntax Highlighting</code> in the <code class=\"language-text\">oh-my-zsh</code> theme.</p>\n<h2 id=\"install-oh-my-zsh-using-curl\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#install-oh-my-zsh-using-curl\" aria-label=\"install oh my zsh using curl permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Install Oh-My-Zsh using Curl:</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sh</span> -c <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token function\">curl</span> -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh/master/tools/install.sh<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\"</span></code></pre></div>\n<br>\n<p><strong>NOTE: <code class=\"language-text\">ZSH</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">OhMyZsh</code> both are different.</strong></p>\n<p>Letâ€™s take a look how to install plugins, and configure <code class=\"language-text\">Zsh</code>:</p>\n<h2 id=\"install-zsh-autosuggestions-by-running\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#install-zsh-autosuggestions-by-running\" aria-label=\"install zsh autosuggestions by running permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Install zsh-autosuggestions by running:</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> clone https://github.com/zsh-users/zsh-autosuggestions.git <span class=\"token variable\">$ZSH_CUSTOM</span>/plugins/zsh-autosuggestions</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"install-zsh-syntax-highlighting-by-running\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#install-zsh-syntax-highlighting-by-running\" aria-label=\"install zsh syntax highlighting by running permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Install zsh-syntax-highlighting by running:</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> clone https://github.com/zsh-users/zsh-syntax-highlighting.git <span class=\"token variable\">$ZSH_CUSTOM</span>/plugins/zsh-syntax-highlighting</code></pre></div>\n<br>\n<p>Now, open <code class=\"language-text\">.zshrc</code> file with your favourite editor:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">nano</span> ~/.zshrc</code></pre></div>\n<br>\n<p>And simply add <code class=\"language-text\">zsh-autosuggestions</code> &#x26; <code class=\"language-text\">zsh-syntax-highlighting</code> to <code class=\"language-text\">plugins()</code> section, it will do the magic for you:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token assign-left variable\">plugins</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>git zsh-autosuggestions zsh-syntax-highlighting<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<br>\n<p>Reopen terminal to reconfigure the settings and Voila! ðŸŽ‰</p>","timeToRead":1,"frontmatter":{"title":"How to customize Oh My Zsh with Auto-Suggestions and Syntax Highlighting?","date":"October 06, 2020","description":"As a developer, we spend a lot of time working on the terminal and having personalized shell makes the working environment perfect, decreases frustration and also, increases productivity.","tags":["ohmyzsh","git","plugin","themes"],"disqus":true},"fields":{"langKey":"en"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/auto-suggestions-and-syntax-highlighting/","previous":null,"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/firefox-mercurial/","langKey":"en","directoryName":"firefox-mercurial"},"frontmatter":{"date":"September 08, 2020","title":"Mercurial Guide for FirefoxÂ Workflow","tags":["open-source","mercurial","firefox","mozilla"]}},"previousInSameTag":null,"nextInSameTag":null,"translationsLink":[]}},"staticQueryHashes":["1522010811","2478439695","2894998521","3765107650","592141294"]}